The paper introduces a new conditional probability flow-based model for generative modeling that exploits attributes to learn tight conditional priors around manifolds of target observations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
